PN,36707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F367A1774541484
OL,3,CMan who talked down hospital bomber on
OL,4,Cvape break 'was just meant to be there'
OL,6,FNathan Newby is as down-to-earth as
OL,7,Fthey come. There are no airs or graces
OL,8,Fabout him, and he's visibly
OL,9,Funcomfortable with the spotlight now
OL,10,Fturned on him. When we met, he was
OL,11,Fquick to downplay his involvement,
OL,12,Finsisting he was simply "in the right
OL,13,Fplace at the right time." But on the
OL,14,Fearly morning of January 20th, 2023,
OL,15,FNathan was more than just a bystander;
OL,16,Fhe was the only thing standing between
OL,17,Fa hospital and a catastrophe.Nathan
OL,18,Fwas a patient at St James's Hospital
OL,19,Fthat night, receiving care for his
OL,20,Fmental health. He had stepped outside
OL,21,Ffor a vape in the early hours when he
OL,22,Fcrossed paths with Mohammed Farooq.
OL,23,FFate is a strange thing`Nathan told me
OL,24,Fthat had he stayed in his hospital
OL,25,Froom at the front of the building, the
OL,26,Fplanned explosion likely would have
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G7/8
